<h2 id="positions">Positions</h2>

<p>To change the position of the image, simply set the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">position</code> parameter to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">left</code> or <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">right</code> - middle is the default.  Here are some examples:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><figcaption class="code">Code snippet</figcaption><pre><code class="language-liquid" data-lang="liquid"><span class="p">{%</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nt">include</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nv">image</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="na">file</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"cute_dog.png"</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="na">position</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s2">"left"</span><span class="p">%}</span></code></pre></figure>

